  "prompt": "What are the branch options for 7k rank holders in manipal institute of technology entrance exam?",
  "response": "The options available for a candidate with a 7k rank in the Manipal Institute of Technology (MIT) entrance exam (also known as MET) can vary each year depending on several factors, including the number of candidates, overall performance, and demand for specific branches. While I don't have the latest data past October 2023, historically, a rank of around 7k could offer opportunities in various engineering branches.\n\nCommon branches that might be available for candidates with a rank in that range include:\n\n1. **Civil Engineering**\n2. **Mechanical Engineering**\n3. **Electrical and Electronics Engineering**\n4. **Electronics and Communication Engineering**\n5. **Computer Science and Engineering**\n6. **Information Technology**\n7. **Biotechnology**\n8. **Chemical Engineering**\n\nHowever, the availability of these branches can change every year. It's essential to check the official MIT website or contact their admissions office for the most current and accurate information regarding branch availability for your specific rank. Additionally, candidates should also keep an eye on the official counseling process to make informed decisions based on real-time data.",
